so the hate list is so short everyone will be getting rampaged<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Not true. IME SoV mobs only rampage one target (but the rampage list has more than one slot), I don't have much experience on SoL mobs but from what I've heard they vary between 1 and 4 rampage targets. People reporting multiple rampage targets (at the same time) on something like Vindi are getting confused with riposte damage or hate list aggro switching during the fight.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
This could also explain why someone getting rampaged can back out of a fight and stop getting rampaged (they become totally removed from hate list), re-engage (clean slate so at bottom of hate), and are suddenly taking rampage yet again.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That would also assume other people who aren't generating aggro are not in prox aggro range, you don't need to damage a mob to get on it's hate list. According to your theory when that person backs out the next person who in lowest on the hate list and still in rampage range would be the new target - IME this is not true. When rampage targets do change (from the assigned rampage tank) it tends to go to monks, rogues, and clerics IME, all classes that are typically high on the hate list.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
What would be good proof is if upon engaging a rampage mob, 5 warriors hit it but only the main tank continued fighting, the rest just stood there. If my theory is true then they would take rampage the entire fight by simply being on the bottom of the hate list.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don't see how this proves your theory. It equally 'proves' the theory the rampage list is separate and, once created, is much less dynamic than the hate list so once you are on it you won't get off it just by not attacking you need to wait until the rampage list is refreshed. I would bet money on a fight lasting more than a couple of minutes they would not remain on the rampage list (assuming there are others generating hate not just the MT). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uemodius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Emodius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/8/02 7:25:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10985.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thoughts on rampage.</span><hr size=1> Guessing games are fun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showPrevMessage?topicID=10985.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showNextMessage?topicID=10985.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10985.topic&index=15><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.emailToFriend?topicID=10985.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/f